=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_IFFT_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright gritty sound, with complex oscillator character around 51 Hz, featuring moderate attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: moderate
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: gritty
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 50.8740
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.0447
  harmonic_regularity: 0.1830
  pitch_clarity: 3.8252
  inharmonicity: 0.0270
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -0.0361
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: IFFT Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/IFFT.html
// Tags: IFFT, Classes, spectral
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
// without any modification, convert FFT chain (frequency domain signal) back to audio (time domain signal)
(
{   var in, chain;
    in = WhiteNoise.ar;
    chain = FFT(LocalBuf(2048), in);
    IFFT.ar(chain) * -20.dbamp // inverse FFT
}.play;
)
